 when working to remedy\ndefects. That said, teams' expression of attitudes was not found to be a strong\npredictor of their task completion performance. Conclusion: Efforts aimed at\nreducing bug incidence may positively limit teams' emotional disposition when\nresolving bugs, thereby reducing the otherwise high demand for emotionally\nstable members. (Abridged)\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 25 Apr 2021 11:15:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-04-27"}
